<P>
   REPUBS-ABORTION _ The Republican Party establishment has
undergone a fundamental repositioning, and softening, of its stand
on abortion, recognizing that a more tolerant position on perhaps
the most divisive issue in American politics is imperative to their
hopes of reclaiming the White House. By Richard L. Berke.
