</P>
<P>
   SECRET-SERVICE-SHOOTINGS _ The people who protect the president
have turned their attention to school violence. Spurred by the
killings in April of 12 students and a teacher in Littleton, Colo.,
a Secret Service team has begun a detailed review of earlier cases,
interviewing as many of the killers as it can. Instead of focusing
on ``troubled kids,'' the Secret Service is looking for patterns of
motive and behavior. The goal is to help schools and the police
recognize which students are moving from interest in murder to the
idea of murder to weapons acquisition.
</P>
