<SLUG> BC-KID-TECH22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Doll House's activities fun for young girls
 &HT;    By Yusuf Davis
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ From the Fisher-Price Time to Play series, Doll House
is girls-only activity software that is kid-friendly and full of
fun, said 4-year-old Rebekah Farris.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was fun,'' said the youngster from suburban Atlanta, who
reviewed the game with the help of her mother, Joy Farris. ``I like
it.''
</P>
<P>
   After getting started with a little help from mom, Rebekah was
able to use the mouse and play with Doll House on her own.
</P>
<P>
   ``It told me everything to do,'' she said of the easy-to-use
program.
</P>
<P>
   The goal of this role-playing program is to select one of four
multicultural dolls and complete activities in each of five rooms,
with different themes. With the help of Glitter, the fairy guide,
girls do everything from decorate a cake to clean and polish a
room. By completing each activity, girls collect items needed to
hold a first-birthday party for little brother.
</P>
<P>
   Rebekah's favorite activity was playing `dress up' in big
sister's room.
</P>
<P>
   ``I like to dress up the doll,'' said Rebekah, who got to choose
from a closet full of outfits to dress for any occasion. Or, if she
didn't like what was available, she could create her own outfits
and leave them on the screen or print them out.
</P>
<P>
   Whenever she can wrestle one of two family computers from her
bigger brothers, Rebekah likes to navigate the full-of-surprises
virtual mansion, which resembles the 3-D doll house she owns.
</P>
<P>
   ``She plays it as much as any other program she has,'' Joy
Farris said.
</P>
<P>
   Doll House gets high marks from Rebekah and her mom. They said
the graphics, animation and soundtrack were adequate, though not
overwhelming.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's pretty cute and a definite girl thing,'' Joy Farris said.
``It's really good for the 4- to 7-year-old age group it was meant
for.''
</P>
<P>
   DOLL HOUSE
</P>
<P>
   Developer: Fisher-Price
</P>
<P>
   Price: $19.95
</P>
<P>
   Format: PC and Mac
</P>
<P>
   Rebekah's grade: A
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
