   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-ACCESS _ AUSTIN _ Phone line, cable or wireless? When
it comes to getting plugged into the Internet, the choices are
growing almost daily. We take a look at the pros and cons of the
most popular types of Internet access and tell readers why the
choices might be changing. (Gallaga, Austin American-Statesman).
MOVED FRIDAY, JUNE 18.
</P>
<P>
   AUS-TECHNOPHOTOS _ The line between your glossy photos and
images stored on your PC may blur with better software for
archiving your photos, falling prices for scanners and digital
cameras and, even digital picture frames. (Gallaga, Austin
American-Statesman). MOVED FRIDAY, JUNE 18.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PERSONAL TECHNOLOGY PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDS: This is the CoxNet PTECH page for the current week. This
layout is available Tuesday after 2 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH 0622 _ The same advances in technology that shrank
workplace tools such as cell phones and computers now invading the
world of workouts. (Gallaga, Austin American-Statesman) Art
includes one 3-column color photo of a workout guy covered with
high-tech gear, a 2 column photo of a neck cooler, a 1-column color
photo of an anti-bug band, an 18-pica color photo of a heart
monitor and an 18-pica color photo of a distance measurer.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TECH BRIEFS _ Broderbund released an updated version of its
genealogy software, the Family Tree Maker Deluxe 15-CD set. It
includes a different type of family tree, one that includes
everyone entered into the family file, not just blood relatives.
(Staff, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes one 18-pica
color photo of Family Tree software.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY _ Here are some really basic tips that will make
e-mail more fun and that will increase the likelihood of a long and
interesting conversation. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.)
Art includes 1 column color sig of columnist.
</P>
<P>
   TECHTOOLS -_ IBM's venture into the world of DVD, the 1999 World
Book Family Reference Suite, is a pretty good tool hampered by
exceptionally poor organization. (Warner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.)
</P>
<P>
   HOME-THEATER _ ATLANTA _ Is it the startling appeal of new
theaters with stadium seating and razzle-dazzle surround sound _ or
maybe the never-ending quest for affordable popcorn? For whatever
reason, the idea of creating a little theater of your own, in your
house, continues to grow and build. (Holsendolph, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY_ Popular column about personal computing written for
the average user. This week: Remember MP3 _ it's a pioneer. (Eds:
