<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Harry Potter casts new spell
 &HT;    By Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Harry Potter is back for his second year at Hogwarts School for
Witchcraft and Wizardry _ and already he's in trouble! A spirit
named Moaning Myrtle, who haunts the girls' bathroom, and the
unwanted attentions of Ron Weasley's sister are minor problems
compared to someone turning students into stone! ``Harry Potter and
the Chamber of Secrets,'' the second book in the series, was
released three months early in the United States. Check libraries
and bookstores now ($17.95, Scholastic Press). Stay tuned to NFK
for more about ``Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets.''
</P>
<P>
   Women's World Cup kicks in
</P>
<P>
   Eyes from around the soccer-loving world are focused on the
United States this week, as the 1999 Women's World Cup begins.
Champions in 1991, the U.S. team will try again. The championship
began Saturday and will run through July 10. Games will be
televised Wednesdays, Thursdays, Saturdays and Sundays, rotating
among ABC, ESPN and ESPN2. You can watch the U.S. take on Nigeria
at 8:30 p.m. Thursday on ESPN.
</P>
<P>
   Defend your body
</P>
<P>
   Your body is a battleground, and Team Antioxidant is one of its
best defenders. You've never heard of it? Well, maybe you know its
members better as Vitamin E, Vitamin C and the Carotenoids. If
you're still confused, head to the SciTrek Museum through July 6 to
learn about good nutrition. You can play with the interactive
exhibit and learn how to send away for a cool poster. For a free
copy of the poster, send a self-addressed, stamped envelope to Team
Antioxidant, 3550 Young Place, Lynchburg, VA 24501.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
