2-0, in the NBA Finals, the first time they have been in a
desperate situation in the playoffs since the do-or-die Game 5 of
the first-round series against Miami. So will the crowd, feeling
that sense of desperation, try to become the Knicks' sixth man?
Will the fans will the Knicks to score more points and possibly
intimidate the Spurs and maybe even get the refs to give the Knicks
as many chances at the foul line as they've given San Antonio? By
