<HEADLINE>
STRAPLESS IN THE DAYTIME 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Strapless dresses are the No. 1 choice of the young
crowd for evening, but in summer strapless styles come out by day
as well. They can even be worn to the office, sheltered by a
cardigan or jacket.
</P>
<P>
   Strapless tube tops are versatile enough to wear with skirts,
pants or suits. Saks Fifth Avenue has tube tops by Linda Allard for
Ellen Tracy in hot pink ($105); by DKNY in petal pink and lime
lightweight polyester meant for layering ($45 each); by Lafayette
New York 148 in black or brown ($118), and by Laundry in olive,
black, white or blue knitted cotton with matching shrugs ($98
each). Barneys New York has knit tubes in black, white, light blue
or camel ($150).
</P>
<P>
   Bergdorf Goodman has short strapless dresses by Theory in khaki
($195); by DKNY in black ($145), and by Calvin Klein in black
($850), as well as DKNY's tube ($85) and matching cropped cardigan
($125) in black, peach, lavender or gray.  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
