<P>
   CENT: A recent Census Bureau report finds the nation's
centenarian population overwhelmingly female and doubling this
decade. Women living in the Midwest have the best chance of living
to 100. Kansas, Iowa and Nebraska were among the six states with
the highest percentages of centenarians. Missouri was 13th. We
interview local centenarians for their secrets of long life and
aging experts (or experts on aging) to find out what makes the
Midwest, and women, so lucky. Alan Bavley and Lee Hill Kavanaugh.
50. Photos; graphic.
</P>
