   FASHION-SANDALS:Open-toed sandals appropriate for the office?
How do you combine summer casual with professional in a time when
fewer women are wearing hosiery and sandals are the rage... Some
image people advise against toe show with business attire....but
some people acknowledge the times they are changing... Jackie
White. Art available.
</P>
<P>
   TARZAN-ANIMATOR: The world didn't need another Tarzan movie.
</P>
<P>
   At least that's what animator Kevin Lima thought four years ago.
The Walt Disney Co. had offered him the chance to co-direct a
cartoon version of the familiar yarn about an orphaned Englishman
raised from infancy by a family of great apes.
</P>
<P>
   ``Then I went back and read the book, Edgar Rice Burroughs'
Tarzan of the Apes. And I was so glad I did, because it's a great
template for an animated film.'' It takes only a few seconds of
Tarzan's spectacular tree-surfing to convince audiences that this
animated Tarzan has some of the coolest moves around. But patrons
who show up for the spectacle find themselves gripped as well by
some serious drama. Robert W. Butler.
</P>
<P>
   BUGS-SEASON: Mosquitoes and wasps. Chiggers and grubs. Cicadas.
Aphids. Spiders. And crickets. Summer's the busiest season for
bugs, bugs and more bugs. Yet, this season _ as you spray, swat and
shoo them, as you listen to their songs, discover them under rocks,
smile at their antics in gardens and even flee from a few _ ask
yourself: How well do you really know them? Eric Adler. 40 inches.
Art.
</P>
<P>
   BUGS-FLICKS: with Bugs-season. List of movies featuring large
infestations. Robert Trussell. 7 inches.
