<HEADLINE>
HELLESTRAE GETS ONE-YEAR DEAL FROM COWBOYS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Deep snapper Dale Hellestrae has agreed to a
one-year contract worth $400,000 with the Cowboys.
</P>
<P>
   Hellestrae's signing represents a change in thinking by the
Cowboys, who earlier this spring had considered going with a
younger, less expensive player at the position.
</P>
<P>
   However, that was before Cowboys coach Chan Gailey called
Hellestrae's agent Steve Weinberg last week and said the Cowboys
would like to bring Hellestrae back.
</P>
<P>
   Weinberg said Hellestrae, a 14-year veteran who played the past
nine years with the Cowboys, is pleased, as he will head into
training camp with a chance to retain his role as the team's deep
snapper.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys also signed a fourth quarterback, rookie free-agent
Brian Kuklick of Wake Forest. Kuklick, 6-foot-5 and 205 pounds,
will compete with Mike Quinn for the third quarterback spot behind
Troy Aikman and Jason Garrett.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys also announced they have released cornerback Omar
Turner of Montana State and offensive lineman Brad Winn of North
Texas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-21-99 2022EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
