   By Tom Paulson. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FOREST-MERGER (Seattle) _ Two of the oldest names in the Pacific
Northwest's forest products industry are combining to form one of
the world's largest timber, lumber and paper companies.
Weyerhaeuser Co., based in Federal Way, Wash, is buying MacMillan
Bloedel, headquartered in Vancouver, B.C., in a stock deal valued
at about $2.5 billion.
</P>
