EXPERIMENTAL-PATIENTS-1 6-21 -- Carole Danforth at home
administering her asthma medication. After finding helpful
medication for her asthma in a drug trial program, Ms. Danforth has
become part of a growing number of drug-trial nomads wandering from
study to study. ``I can't keep track of them all,'' Ms. Danforth
said of the drug studies in which she has participated. ``But I
haven't felt this good in a long time.'' (Evan Richman/New York
