<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JAFRA-LAYOFFS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JAFRA COSMETICS RELOCATES, LAYS OFF WORKERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY CECILIA CHAN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   THOUSAND OAKS, Calif. _ An international &UR;  &LR; cosmetics company
founded by a husband-and-wife team 43 years ago &UR;  &LR; has relocated its
Ventura County operations and laid off nearly one-fourth of its
employees, officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Jafra Cosmetics International has contracted out the
manufacturing of its skin and body care products to an unidentified
Southern California firm to improve competitiveness, according to a
company statement.
</P>
<P>
   The company's termination of 75 employees, including 14
managerial and technical workers and 61 others, becomes effective
60 days from June 10 of this year, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Officials with the Thousand Oaks company were out of the state
and unavailable for comment.
</P>
<P>
   City officials hope to soften the blow of the company's actions
by luring another company to the site, prime freeway-front property
off the Ventura Freeway.
</P>
<P>
   ``We certainly are going to miss them,'' said Gary Wartik,
manager of economic development for Thousand Oaks. ``The property
they own is very prime property. It's a nice area with medium- and
high-tech businesses.''
</P>
<P>
   Wartik said he is working with a company from the San Fernando
Valley, which he declined to name, that is interested in relocating
to Thousand Oaks.
</P>
<P>
   He said the business, which is looking for a building with
office and storage space and shipping capability, likely would be
interested in the Jafra site.
</P>
<P>
   ``We certainly want to make sure property like that doesn't stay
vacant long,'' Wartik said. ``We want to maintain the ability of
Ventura County and Thousand Oaks to attract companies from outside
the area and add to the economic base.''
</P>
<P>
   The relocation is not expected to be felt among the company's
self-employed sales force.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jafra's independent sales force will not be impacted by this
action Jafra is taking,'' the statement read. ``Jafra is retaining
quality assurance, planning, purchasing and research and
development functions.''
</P>
<P>
   Jafra operates primarily in the United States but has
subsidiariesin 11 countries. Last year its self-employed direct
sales consultants numbered 262,800 worldwide, of which 56,500 are
in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   The Jafra site has been a fixture in the community for years.
The company's 317 employees handled manufacturing and distribution
from the Townsgate Road facility.
</P>
<P>
   The company will pay all laid-off employees salary and benefits
through the 60-day period, according to a company letter notifying
the city of the move as required by federal law.
</P>
<P>
   The company also has paid each affected employee $1,000 and
offered each a severance payment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
